Brands are pretty good at creating service and sales support content, like product FAQs. But they struggle in two crucial areas:

â€œThought leadershipâ€ content that engages readers who are not already in the sales funnel or, as I said, drinking the corporate Kool-Aid. This content is vitally important for reaching new prospects and earning trust (see my piece, Why the informed buyer is ruining the content party).
